.TH TVDINNER 1 "July 2026" "tvdinner 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tvdinner \- play IPTV streams from an M3U playlist, with XMLTV EPG overlay and guide
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tvdinner
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIURL\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tvdinner
plays IPTV streams from an M3U/M3U8 playlist (or a direct video/audio stream
URL) using mpv. \fIURL\fR may be an http(s) URL or a local file path.
.PP
If \fIURL\fR looks like an M3U playlist, its channels are listed and one can
be selected interactively, or directly via \fB\-\-channel\fR. Otherwise
\fIURL\fR is played directly as a stream.
.PP
EPG (electronic programme guide) data is drawn automatically from the
playlist's own embedded XMLTV reference where available, or from an
explicit \fB\-\-epg\fR URL. EPG times are timezone-aware and can be
corrected with \fB\-\-time-shift\fR for feeds that report incorrect times.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Show a help message and exit.
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-channel\fR \fICHANNEL\fR
Channel name (or 1-based index) to play directly, skipping interactive
selection.
.TP
\fB\-\-list\fR
List channels in the playlist and exit without playing.
.TP
\fB\-\-epg\fR \fIURL\fR
XMLTV EPG URL or local file, overriding any EPG source discovered in the
M3U playlist.
.TP
\fB\-\-tz\fR \fINAME\fR
IANA timezone for displaying EPG times, e.g. \fIEurope/London\fR (default:
system local timezone).
.TP
\fB\-\-time\-shift\fR \fISHIFT\fR
Correct EPG feed clock errors, e.g. \fI+1h\fR, \fI\-30m\fR, or minutes as a
plain integer.
.SH KEYS
While a stream is playing, in addition to mpv's own default key bindings:
.TP
.B i
Show the current/next programme info overlay.
.TP
.B g
Toggle the full program guide.
.TP
.B LEFT / RIGHT
Page the program guide's timeline back/forward by 30 minutes (guide only;
otherwise these seek the video as usual).
.TP
.B UP / DOWN
Move the program guide's channel selection cursor (guide only).
.TP
.B ENTER
Show full details for the selected guide programme.
.TP
.B ESC
Close the programme details popup.
.TP
.B z
Cycle the video's display aspect ratio (Auto, 4:3, 16:9, 2.35:1, 1:1).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
List the channels in a playlist:
.B tvdinner https://example.com/playlist.m3u \-\-list
.TP
Play a channel directly by name:
.B tvdinner playlist.m3u \-\-channel "BBC One"
.TP
Play a direct stream URL:
.B tvdinner https://example.com/stream.m3u8
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mpv (1)
